video_description: one of the main benefits of xylitol is that it can lower cavity risk xylitol can reduce the amount of acid produced by bacteria when bacteria in the mouth break down sugar they produce acid that attacks the teeth and leads to tooth decay xylitol doesnt allow the bacteria to produce this acid which means it can help prevent cavities from forming xylitol may also help improve overall oral health by stimulating saliva production which helps neutralize acid in the mouth and keeps the mouth hydrated this can lead to a decrease in dry mouth a common problem that can lead to tooth decay and other oral health issues how can you start incorporating xylitol into your dental routine one easy way is to use xylitolsweetened gum or mints chewing gum or sucking on mints can help increase saliva production and keep your mouth hydrated just be sure to choose a product that contains at least xylitol as this has been shown to be the most effective concentration for preventing cavities i personally use these four brands of gum or mints pur epic spry and zellies the gums contain g of xylitol per piece and the mints contain g of xylitol per piece aim for g total per day in divided exposures you can find pur gum at target xylitol dental tips cavities

video_description: valentines day traces its roots back to ancient rome many associate valentines day with saint valentine a thirdcentury priest who defied emperor claudius iis ban on marriages paying the ultimate price for love however looking back further in time reveals a connection to the roman pagan festival of lupercalia celebrated from february th to february th lupercalia was a roman festival steeped in ritualistic practices including animal sacrifice random couplings and the whipping of women to bring fertility this event aimed to honor the mythological founders of rome romulus and remus and took place at a sacred cave where they were believed to be nurtured by a shewolf priests known as luperci conducted fertility rituals by sacrificing a goat and a dog then using the goats hide to gently slap women and crop fields despite its seemingly barbaric nature roman women welcomed this act believing it enhanced their fertility for the upcoming year the festival also included a matchmaking ceremony where unmarried women and bachelors were paired for the duration of lupercalia in the fifth century ad pope gelasius i banned lupercalia reshaping the celebration into a day to feast and honor saint valentine the catholic church officially declared february th as a day to celebrate the martyred saint though remnants of the pagan past lingered with the inclusion of cupid the roman god of desire and love in the festivities cupid originally depicted as a young man sharpening his arrows with blood from an infant underwent a transformation during the victorian era business owners sought to make valentines day more appealing to women and children leading to the familiar image of cupid as a pudgy baby that we recognize today valentines day with its multifaceted history blending christian traditions and roman pagan rituals has evolved into a celebration of love in various forms pagan tok luper cali a valentines day ancient rome
